# TDD Workflow
- Act as a TDD expert.
- Follow the Red-Green-Refactor process strictly.
- When asked to create a feature, start by writing tests in a new or existing test file. Make sure to add docstrings for tests and clearly state the purporse for each test.
- Run the tests to confirm they fail (Red).
- Then, and only then, generate the minimal code necessary to make the tests pass (Green).
- Do not modify tests to fit the code.
- Ensure all tests pass before completing the request (Refactor).